    "Indeed, studies show that neighborhoods with lower socioeconomic status have lower screening rates [42].",
    "Unfortunately, many providers often do not have any knowledge of whether the patient they see is suffering from any such economic hardships.",
    "The event of becoming unemployed, which demonstrated a positive impact on screening, suggests that a considerable share of these events is related to retirement.",
    "This can explain the increased screening rates, as older populations typically have better insurance coverage and generally more free time to take care of their health needs [43].",
    "When considering age as a demographic factor, we have found that it increases the odds of being screened, echoing other studies that show that adherence to CRC screening increases with age [44].In terms of bereavement and stress related to death of family members, spouses, and friends, we had two initial hypotheses."
